DJ TIRA and his wife, Gugu Khathi, brought their families and friends together yesterday.As part of the traditional wedding process, Gugu hosted an umbondo ceremony at Tira&rsquo;s KwaHlabisa homestead, in KZN.The ceremony started around 4.30pm.Gugu said: &ldquo;We&rsquo;ve been preparing for this day for some time.&ldquo;Tira&rsquo;s family is a very warm family.&rdquo;DJ Tira praised Gugu for being a wonderful and respectful wife.&ldquo;Since I met my wife, I learnt to be humble and I also learnt to respect other people. &ldquo;What we&rsquo;re doing today is part of our tradition. &ldquo;She&rsquo;s bringing umbondo. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re not rushing, because we&rsquo;re happy. &ldquo;Maybe next year, we&rsquo;ll do our white wedding. &ldquo;But we had to do this first,&rdquo; the groom said.